review_text: Local bank centers have good people.  Online support is a nightmare since they merged with Sterling Bank in June 2023.  Their website and phone support are horrible.  Long wait times on hold, and no one in customer service knows anything about their "new" platform.  They ask a million questions for security purposes, and then transfer you, and then you will get asked the same million questions and then transferred, and round and round it goes with them repeating your question, but not answering it.  Customer "Support" blames Customer "Service"....  BRUTAL

I mostly use the Black Rock Tpke branch and there is not one negative thing that I can say.  The customer service is outstanding, the Manager, Eric is and has always been a great help to me in many situations where I needed it.  He's become a friend...I've been dealing with him when he was working at the Post Road branch, and will continue to do so.

I do most of my personal banking online but the business banking takes me into the branch almost daily.  There isn't one person in this branch that doesn't ask me how I am doing on any given day.  You guys are the best!
